{{Quote|Gods, &lt;u&gt;this&lt;/u&gt; is country!|[[Robert Baratheon]]|Winter is Coming}}
The '''Barrowlands''' are a region in [[the North]], located to the east of [[the Rills]] and southwest of [[Winterfell]]. The [[Kingsroad]] passes through the eastern edge of the Barrowlands. The town of [[Barrowton]] lies within the Barrowlands and is the largest settlement in the area.&lt;ref&gt;[http://viewers-guide.hbo.com/game-of-thrones/season2/#!/locations/torrhens-square/ HBO viewers guide, season 2 map, Torrhen's Square entry]&lt;/ref&gt;

sections.History:
[[File:Robert-Baratheon-game-of-thrones-19598756-1280-720.jpg|thumb|left|250px|[[Robert Baratheon]] with [[Eddard Stark]] in the Barrowlands.]]
===[[Season 1]]===
[[Eddard Stark]] and [[Robert Baratheon]] hold a meeting in this area on their way south, discussing the marriage of [[Daenerys Targaryen]] to Khal [[Drogo]]. Robert is impressed with the countryside.&lt;ref&gt;[[Winter is Coming (episode)]]&lt;/ref&gt;
